        "title": "Risks of Direct Confrontation",
        "message": "While it's natural to want to defend your child, directly confronting cyberbullies or their parents can backfire in several ways:\n\n- It may embarrass your child and damage their trust in you\n- Bullies often intensify harassment when confronted by parents\n- You risk escalating the situation beyond your control\n- It could create new problems if parents become defensive\n- Your child loses agency in resolving their own situation\n\nInstead, work with proper authorities and social media platforms through official channels, while respecting your child's input on how to proceed.",
